GOODBYE 2022… you were a TOUGH year! 
A LOT of loss… my aunt, my cousin, my sweet pup, and choosing to end a 6 year relationship… love and letting go.
.

From the epitome of darkness is self discovery. It’s where we find truth and where we grow. Coming out and stepping into the light there’s a greater understanding of gratitude. It’s quite astonishing how humans can feel the spectrum. From the same place of pain there is pleasure, our minds are powerful enough to make the switch and choose to learn and be happy. I’m so grateful for this life and all it’s lessons. 🙏❤️
.
HELLO 2023… I welcome you… I’m ready… STANDING TALL AND FEELING SUPPORTED. I’m stronger, wiser, and happier. This year it’s all about doubling down on ME and living an even healthier lifestyle. As most of you know about me, I’m a HUGE believer in the healing power of mushrooms. I’m so grateful to be a brand ambassador for @supermush. Spreading the love of mushrooms and how they truly support our physical and mental health. Health is wealth…. let’s continue to normalize these conversations and guide one another wherever we’re at on our healing journeys. Here’s to a new year! Much love! ❤️🙏
.
SIDE NOTE: I’m literally obsessed with ALL my SuperMush gear! So of course I’m rocking my Live in Color shorts for the 1st day of the year!! lol Also, get ready for a new product coming out!! 👅 #healthiswealth #supermush #happynewyear 
.

THE HOME WITHIN
.

IF all that failed turned to dust and blew beneath the chambered door, would you still cast a stone?

IF the ship wrecked shore was cleared of sight and the sea was calmed at heart, would you still care to see the light?

IF all else matters lies outside accepting arms and focus began to come astray, would you still hear the silence?

CONTINUE on this journey, try another door. The sand that clings to this layer, will be carried gently through the storm.

TO brave the everlasting feeling, defending it's magical sound. This is where you'll find me, rediscovered and dancing with the wind.

BE moved by the music, care less to be followed by the crowd. Release beliefs hindering you from connecting and living your intention.

INSPIRED by your inner beauty, understand it’s where you live. The most sacred space we carry with us, is the home we build within. 

.

This past 18 months has been the most challenging of my life. So much loss, so much heartache. Feeling disconnected from my mind and body. At times I would get stuck in the IFs and forgetting to CONTINUE TO BE INSPIRED by ME! All of my loss, gain, pain, pleasure, fails, and wins… I’ll use all of it as fuel to become the driving force for what lies ahead, shaping my perspective, resilience, and determination. Each triumph, challenge, and setback has played a vital role in shaping my character and guiding my choices. Now, with this new lens of deep compassion and gratitude I shall continue to build THE HOME WITHIN.

“I am a necessary part of an important search to which there is no end.”- Keith Haring
.

The heart portrayed in Keith Haring’s work reflects his belief in humanity and the power of love. We are forever soul searching, because we’re changing. We’re growing deeper into our roots. Both self-discovery and self-love are powerful tools for connecting people. When individuals learn to understand and accept themselves, they become more empathetic and compassionate toward others. Love has the capacity to unite humanity. 
#love #loveismyreligion #selflove #selfexpression #keithharing #loveislove

We don’t have to be confined by the roles society assigns us. We can change into whatever form we desire. Change is an essential part of growth. We can break free from those constraints and explore the endless possibilities that lie within our minds. It’s a reminder that we should never stop playing, never stop dreaming, and never stop believing in the magic of our own creativity.
.

My inspiration, Akasha. An ancient and powerful Queen of all vampires in Anne Rice’s “The Vampire Chronicles” series, particularly known for her appearance in the 1988 novel “The Queen of the Damned.” I first discovered this character when the film was later released in 2002, playing the role of Akasha was the “Queen of Urban Pop”Aaliyah. Unfortunately, her life was cut short at the young age of 22 due to a plane crash months after wrapping on the film. A devoted admirer of her work, I was devastated to hear the news. Since then, I have fantasized about embodying this character AND here I am 21 years later making my dreams come true. I wanted to honor her and the character, paying homage to the QUEENS and awakening the queen in ME. 🖤 👑 
.
HUGE thank you to @davidmnorton for supporting my wild vision, and going on a journey with me to make everything by hand🤪 So much love and gratitude 🖤🙏 #akasha #aaliyah#queenofthedamned #queenofurbanhiphop #queenofhiphop
